This paper discusses the performance evaluation of persistent memory (PMem) technologies in the context of disk-based database systems, which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the development of I/O primitives tuned for PMem, which could fall under the categories of architecture (cs.AR) and operating systems (cs.OS). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential impact of PMem on system design and performance, which could fall under the categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and systems and control (cs.SY).
